        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">616 818 5413</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Logline</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">In a last-ditch effort to reinvent herself, a struggling educator tries to secure a role in an educational television series that defined many childhoods, only to face the misinformed public and shadow of the original host.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Episode</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No"/>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Center" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Underline">Plot Summary</Text>
      </Paragraph>
      <Paragraph Alignment="Full" FirstIndent="0.00" Leading="Regular" LeftIndent="1.00" OutlineLevel="1" RightIndent="7.50" SpaceBefore="0" Spacing="1" StartsNewPage="No">
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">The episode opens with a 2014 flashback to a theater camp where a Ray and her rival, Aurora, compete for the lead in </Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="Italic">Peter Pan</Text>
        <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">. After the director confuses the two and casts Aurora as the lead, a frustrated Ray (as the sidekick Tinker Bell) accidentally sets the stage on fire.</Text>
      </Paragraph>
    </Content>
